        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Doug Oucharek",
          "email": "doug.s.oucharek@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-04-12 21:21:53.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-3164 utils: Fix Wireshark decode of Lustre under Infiniband",
        "message": "LU-3164 utils: Fix Wireshark decode of Lustre under Infiniband\n\nDue to a difference in the IB LND vs TCP LND header sizes, some\nhard-coded offsets in the LNet dissector will not believe that the\npayload is lustre.  As such, the lustre protocol may not be decoded\nunder Infiniband.\n\nThis patch addresses this by adding a variable to applicable offsets\nwhich is set to 0 for TCP, and 24 (extra bytes in IB LND header)\nfor Infiniband.\n\nSigned-off-by: Doug Oucharek <doug.s.oucharek@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I3783bbb563df109e160752d246db9bc5148cf132\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
